Author: Tasnim Hamza [aut] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4700-6990>),
    Guido Schwarzer [aut, cre] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6214-9087>),
    Georgia Salanti [aut] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3830-8508>)
Maintainer: Guido Schwarzer <sc@imbi.uni-freiburg.de>
Description: Network meta-analysis and meta-regression (allows including
    up to 3 covariates) for individual participant data, aggregate data,
    and mixtures of both formats using the three-level hierarchical model.
    Each format can come from randomized controlled trials or
    non-randomized studies or mixtures of both. Estimates are generated in
    a Bayesian framework using JAGS. The implemented models are described
    by Hamza et al. 2022 <DOI:10.48550/arXiv.2203.06350>.
